# Skewness & kurtosis values
# Skewness tests symmetry of distribution where closeness to 0 means symmetric, left tail gives negative values, right tail gives positive values
# Kurtosis compares distribution shape to Gaussian ideal where 0 means ideal, flatness gives negative values, peakness gives positive values
# We use type "2" methods for determining skewness & kurtosis as used in SAS & SPSS:
# 	skewness: G_1 = g_1 * sqrt(n(n-1)) / (n-2)
# 	kurtosis: G_2 = ((n+1) g_2 + 6) * (n-1) / ((n-2)(n-3))
#
# Formulae source: D. N. Joanes and C. A. Gill (1998), Comparing measures of sample skewness and kurtosis. The Statistician, 47, 183189.
# Details in ?skewness & ?kurtosis for package:e1071

e1071::skewness(bug_level$reopened_count, na.rm=TRUE, 2);
